oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Corner of Maury and Cannon Streets, Looking south, c. late 1930s
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Photograph of the corner of Maury Street and Cannon Street looking south. The area was designated as the site of the J.C. Napier Homes around 1939. Photographed by the Nashville Housing Authority. Forms part of the MDHA Photograph Collection. 1 photograph : b & w.
